## Required report (in your final message / return)

### Docs review (mandatory; identifiers-touched preamble + per-file enumeration)

Format (filenames are illustrative — list whatever your project actually ships, per `00-universal-core.mdc` "Project documentation"):

```
Docs review:

Identifiers touched this task (for change-impact grep sweep):
- <id-1> — <added | renamed from X | removed | behavior changed: <how>>
- <id-2> — <...>
(Or: Identifiers touched: none — N/A: only private/internal refactor.)

Per-file enumeration (every project .md/.txt in scope):
- <root-readme>.md — edited: <one-line summary>
- CHANGELOG.md — edited: appended [X.Y.Z] entry
- docs/<some-spec>.md — checked: ok (no relevant change)
- docs/<subdir>/ (N files) — checked: ok (group: same status for all)
- <vendored-path>/** (N files) — skipped: <reason>
Total: M reviewed, A edited, B ok, C skipped
```

Group `<dir>/ (N files) — <status>` only when every file in the group shares that status. `Total:` must equal the in-scope file count. A file appearing nowhere counts as missing.

### Other sub-reports

- `.gitignore: <unchanged | updated to add: <patterns>>`
- `Secret-leak scan: clean` **or** `Secret-leak scan: BLOCKED on <paths>` (task must be `blocked`)
- `Change-impact grep sweep: <N/A: no user-visible identifier touched | clean | <intentional carryovers and why>>`
